<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<FinalDraft DocumentType="Script" Template="No" Version="5">
<Content>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<Text>INT. BOXING GYM - NIGHT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text>A dimly lit boxing gym in East LA. Heavy bags hang from chains. The sound of leather on canvas echoes through the empty space. IRON DAN REYES (40s, weathered face, hands wrapped in tape) shadowboxes alone in the ring.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text>Sweat drips onto the canvas. His footwork is precise but slow — a fighter past his prime who refuses to accept it.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text>IRON DAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
<Text>(to himself)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text>One more round. Just one more.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text>The gym door SLAMS open. COACH RUIZ (60s, limping, clutching a newspaper) enters.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text>COACH RUIZ</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text>Danny. You gotta see this.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text>He tosses the newspaper into the ring. Dan picks it up. HEADLINE: "CHAMPION CALLS OUT REYES FOR EXHIBITION BOUT."</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text>IRON DAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text>He's twenty-three years old.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text>COACH RUIZ</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text>And he wants you. Not some contender. You. The question is whether you still want it.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text>Dan stares at the headline. His jaw tightens.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text>CUT TO:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<Text>EXT. DAN'S APARTMENT - DAWN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text>A rundown apartment building in Boyle Heights. First light breaks over the rooftops. Dan sits on the fire escape, icing his knuckles. The city is waking up below him.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text>ELENA (O.S.)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text>You didn't come to bed.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text>ELENA REYES (38, scrubs, night-shift tired) leans against the window frame.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text>IRON DAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text>Couldn't sleep.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text>ELENA</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text>Danny, please don't tell me you're thinking about fighting again.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text>IRON DAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text>It's an exhibition. That's all.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text>ELENA</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text>That's what you said about Juárez. You came home with a broken orbital.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text>Silence. Dan peels the ice bag off his knuckles. The skin underneath is raw and scarred.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<Text>INT. BOXING GYM - DAY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text>The gym is alive now. Young fighters train on the bags. Sparring in the ring. Hip-hop rattles from a cheap speaker.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text>Dan enters, gym bag over his shoulder. The young fighters stop and stare. They know who he is.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text>YOUNG FIGHTER</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text>Iron Dan? No way, bro.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text>Dan ignores him. Walks to the back office where Coach Ruiz is reviewing tape on a laptop.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text>IRON DAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text>I'll do it. Eight weeks. You train me like you used to.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text>COACH RUIZ</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text>Danny, I love you, but you're forty years old with bad knees and worse hands. This kid is a killer.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text>IRON DAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text>Then train me to survive him.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text>Ruiz studies Dan's face. Sees something he hasn't seen in years — fire.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text>COACH RUIZ</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text>Monday. Five AM. Don't be late.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<Text>INT./EXT. MOVING CAR - NIGHT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text>Dan drives through the streets of East LA. Streetlights wash over his face. He grips the steering wheel, lost in thought.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text>His phone buzzes on the passenger seat. He glances at it: "MISSED CALL: ELENA (3)."</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text>He turns the phone face-down and keeps driving.</Text>
</Paragraph>
</Content>
</FinalDraft>
